==Old English==
===Etymology===
Via Germanic, from Indo-European ''*penkwe'' ‘five’.  Cognate with Old High German ''fimf, finf'' (German [[fünf]]), Old Saxon ''fīf'' (Dutch [[vijf]]), Old Norse [[fim]]/[[fimm]] (Swedish [[fem]]), Gothic [[𐍆𐌹𐌼𐍆]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[πέντε]], Latin [[quinque]], Sanskrit [[पञ्चन्]].

